reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great little package
reviews.reviewText: I ordered one of these for myself after going on a business trip. With all the chargers, cables, earbuds, memory sticks I needed to find a better way. So I found this on Amazon.It worked so well for me that I purchased a second one for my wife as gift. She loves it as well. Now everything is stored and carried in one package. It's small enough it will fit into her carry bag for work.The material seems sturdy and seems like it will hold up for a long while. Along with the zipper, smooth with no snagging. The storage area has small compartments that can be arranged to your liking or needs.I would recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So cute and sturdy.
reviews.reviewText: I actually bought this for an alternative use than carrying cables. I use it for storing and transporting my little Eton shortwave radio. It fits the radio with ease and also holds the manual and additional antenna I have for it.I could also put extra batteries in it too if needed. It's padded, sturdy, and is great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very neat little case!
reviews.reviewText: This case is relatively nice quality. It is a handy size and holds all the cables and adapters I used to carry in a larger case. The better depth is what makes this case so user friendly. Good value for the price. I would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great size for travel
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I have been using this case to house my chargers and cords for travel. I like it so much that I bought two more for our kids to use when we traveled abroad. The case holds a lot — the video I attached shows everything I put in it, and there is still room for more. The case is also a little stretchy and the zipper has a little give so you can fit items that are slightly too large (like my circular charger).It comes with spacers you can move and attach using Velcro. I took most of them out because it’s not a necessary feature for me, but I do appreciate the flexibility to not have to keep them in there.I also like that it has a handle for easy carrying. The fabric is also really durable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best for day-to-day use
reviews.reviewText: The sisma Travel Cords Organizer has proven to be the perfect companion for my day-to-day life. This small electronic accessories carrying bag is a game-changer when it comes to keeping cables, adapters, USB sticks, and memory cards organized. The 1680D-fabrics ensure durability and protection for all my essential tech accessories. Its compact size is just right for daily use, fitting seamlessly into my bag or pocket. The thoughtful design with multiple compartments makes it easy to find exactly what I need without the hassle of tangled cords. If you're looking for a sleek and practical solution to keep your electronic accessories in order for day-to-day use, the sisma Travel Cords Organizer is an excellent choice. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewText: I’m using this for my PowerShot camera. It’s large enough for the camera, extra battery, charger and cables. Adjustable dividers make it versatile. Attractive, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bag - I bought another
reviews.reviewText: Works perfectly to hold a charging block and a few 3 - 6' cords. I travel extensively for work and I like just being able to grab this pouch and throw it in my backpack. It worked so well that I bought another one so I can keep one with an American charging block and one with an EU charging block, the EU one also having a UK adaptor. This saves me time packing to leave and keeps me from forgetting chargers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bag for cords
reviews.reviewText: I bought these to hold the most often needed cords and chargers for travel. I just keep this loaded up all time with what I would normally need for travel, and then it is less likely to forget a chord or charger you might need (ask me how I know). I actually bought some extra chords so that I can just leave them in the bag. It is compact, yet holds a lot of stuff and has some separators inside that can be moved around as needed.
